import pandas as pd

data = {'col_0': ['a', 'a', 'a', 'a', 'b','b','b'], 'col_1': [-2, -7, 6, 8, -5, 2, 6]}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)
# Clip the values of 'col_1' in rows where 'col_0' equals 'a' within the range -2 to 2
df.loc[df['col_0']=='a','col_1'] =  df.loc[df['col_0']=='a','col_1'].clip(-2,2)
